[SN]TITLE[SN]
East Yorkshire's 'most prolific' fly-tipper jailed

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man described as the most prolific fly-tipper in East Yorkshire has been jailed for a series of offences.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Darren Armishaw, 49, from Hull, advertised as a commercial waste disposal service, but dumped the rubbish across East Yorkshire.
He was jailed for 10 months after pleading guilty at Hull Crown Court to a string of waste disposal offences.
In addition, he was sent to prison for a further five years after admitting a number of distraction burglaries.
